{
  "texts": [
    "• SubjECTive-QA (SQA) (Pardawala et al., 2024) is a manually-annotated dataset focusing on subjectivity and soft misinformation in Earnings Call Transcripts (ECTs), specifically in their long-form QA sessions.",
    "It includes 49,446 annotations across 2,747 QA pairs from 120 ECTs spanning 2007 to 2021.",
    "Each QA pair is labeled on six subjectivity features: Assertive, Cautious, Optimistic, Specific, Clear, and Relevant.",
    "The dataset was benchmarked using RoBERTa-base and Llama-3-70b-Chat, showing varying performance based on feature subjectivity.",
    "Additionally, cross-domain evaluation on White House Press Briefings demonstrated its broader applicability."
  ]
}